<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

The `<$scribe>` widget wraps input widgets and keeps their backing state in sync with a target field. Input widgets bind to a state tiddler exposed via the `<<state>>` variable; the scribe handles the round-trip in both directions, optionally for a nested sub-path inside a JSON-encoded field.

!! Features

* ''`<$scribe>` widget'' — `tiddler` / `field` / `path` (optional, for sub-path) / `type` / `state` (optional)
* ''Pluggable type handlers'' — `module-type: scribetype` modules implementing `fromField(value)` and `toField(text)`
* ''Five handlers ship'' — `text/plain`, `application/json`, `application/x-string-array`, `application/x-tw-date`, `application/x-tw-datetime`
* ''Sub-path syncing inside a JSON field'' — `path="0,caption"` syncs `kind.fields[0].caption`
* ''Empty-state semantics'' — clearing the state deletes the sub-path key (or empties the whole field), so input widgets can "un-set" a property cleanly

!! Schema model

* ''Target tiddler'' — has a field whose value is plain text (text/plain) or a JSON-encoded string (json / string-array)
* ''State tiddler'' — auto-managed at `$:/temp/rimir/scribe/<field>/<path|_>/<target>` unless overridden via `state=`. Holds the human-editable form of the value in its `text` field.

!! Quick start

```
<$scribe tiddler="Task1" field="kind.fields" path="0,caption" type="text/plain">
  <$edit-text tiddler=<<state>> field="text" tag="input"/>
</$scribe>
```

!! Attribution

Pattern inspired by Flibbles' [ext[FieldTranscriberWidget|https://github.com/flibbles/tw5-graph]]; this is an independent reimplementation that adds sub-path support inside JSON-encoded fields and the `application/x-string-array` type handler.

